  "description": "The NIMH Healthy Research Volunteer Dataset is a comprehensive multimodal neuroimaging resource characterizing 1,859 healthy adults through clinical assessments, psychometric measures, neuropsychological testing, structural and functional MRI, diffusion tensor imaging, and magnetoencephalography. This dataset provides unprecedented depth of phenotypic characterization of a healthy population and enables investigations into normal cognition, mood regulation, and brain function across diverse cognitive domains.",
  "methods_description": "Data collection includes online screening questionnaires (demographics, WHODAS 2.0, DSM-5 cross-cutting measures, AUDIT, Edinburgh Handedness Inventory), in-person clinical assessments (History and Physical, SCID-5, KBIT-2), biological measures (blood pressure, complete blood count, viral markers, drug screening), and neuroimaging. MRI protocol includes T1, T2 FLAIR, pCASL, DTI with distortion correction, and resting-state fMRI. MEG includes resting-state, task-based paradigms (faces, scenes, language, motor), and empty room recordings. Participants also complete NIH Toolbox Cognition Battery tasks assessing attention, executive function, episodic memory, and working memory.",
